    '{"merged_steps": ["(A) Get in high plank position on your hands and toes.(B) Shift your weight to your left hand as you turn your body to the right; bend your right leg behind you and extend your right arm up.", "Return to the center and repeat on the opposite side.", "Continue, alternating sides.**Make it easier:** Don’t raise your arm after you bend your leg behind you.**Make it harder:** Balance with your arm and leg extended for two counts."], "sources": [{"source": "wger", "file": "C:\\Users\\kaiqu\\Desktop\\SOMMA\\datasets\\wger-master\\wger\\exercises\\fixtures\\exercise-base-data.json", "steps": ["(A) Get in high plank position on your hands and toes.(B) Shift your weight to your left hand as you turn your body to the right; bend your right leg behind you and extend your right arm up.", "Return to the center and repeat on the opposite side.", "Continue, alternating sides.**Make it easier:** Don’t raise your arm after you bend your leg behind you.**Make it harder:** Balance with your arm and leg extended for two counts."], "description": "(A) Get in high plank position on your hands and toes.(B) Shift your weight to your left hand as you turn your body to the right; bend your right leg behind you and extend your right arm up. Return to the center and repeat on the opposite side. Continue, alternating sides.**Make it easier:** Don’t raise your arm after you bend your leg behind you.**Make it harder:** Balance with your arm and leg extended for two counts."}], "summary": "(A) Get in high plank position on your hands and toes.(B) Shift your weight to your left hand as you turn your body to the right; bend your right leg behind you and extend your right arm up. Return to the center and repeat on the opposite side. Continue, alternating sides.**Make it easier:** Don’t raise your arm after you bend your leg behind you.**Make it harder:** Balance with your arm and leg extended for two counts.", "cues": "(A) Get in high plank position on your hands and toes.(B) 